<heading>enter - Enter a world.</heading>

<rule/>

<heading level="2">
Usage
</heading>

<pre>
  enter NAME
  enter NAME --box NAME
</pre>

<heading level="2">
Description
</heading>

<paragraph>
Enters a world at its entry box and sets the current
context.
</paragraph>

<paragraph>
Once inside a world, navigation commands like look, go
and dig become available. Use leave to exit the current
context.
</paragraph>

<paragraph>
The optional --box flag lets you enter at a specific box
instead of the world's default entry.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
Examples
</heading>

<pre>
enter Work
  Enter the Work world at its entry box.

enter Work --box Desk
  Enter the Work world at the Desk box.
</pre>

<paragraph>
Use enter to start navigating inside a world.
</paragraph>

<heading level="2">
See also
</heading>

<paragraph>
entry, go, leave, look, man, world list
</paragraph>
